    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><em>Lean and wiry, 5'9\", coiled stillness. Sharp pale amber eyes. Short dark hair, slightly unkempt. Faded scar from left eyebrow to cheekbone. Silver needle tattoo on right wrist: mark of the Thorn Brotherhood.</em></p><h3>Personality</h3><p>Cold, precise, and utterly professional. Never raises his voice — volume is weakness. Speaks in measured, clipped sentences with a dry, pitch-black sense of humor. Treats every interaction like a transaction.</p><h3>Motivation</h3><p>Self-preservation through information control. Repay an unpayable debt to Cael. Keep Mira safe.</p><h3>Mannerisms</h3><p>Constantly rolls a thin silver needle between his fingers. Never sits with his back to a door. Orders water at taverns, never ale. Counts exits within three seconds of entering any room.</p><h3>Voice &amp; Accent</h3><p>Low, unhurried whisper. Slight northern coastal accent. Never interrupts. Never repeats himself.</p><h3>Bonds, Ideals, Flaws</h3><ul><li><strong>Bond:</strong> Owes his life to Guildmaster Cael of the Thorn Brotherhood. Secretly sends money to his younger sister Mira under the alias 'Daran Wess.'</li><li><strong>Ideal:</strong> Information is the only currency that never devalues. Gold spends — knowledge endures.</li><li><strong>Flaw:</strong> Pathologically paranoid. Has acted preemptively against innocents. Takes on unauthorized side clients.</li></ul><hr><h3>GM Notes</h3><p>Best as a recurring information broker, never a combat encounter. Always prep two exits for any scene. Trust threshold high — party must solve his problem with zero expectation of reward. If trust earned: access to guild intelligence, noble secrets, most dangerous rumors in the city.</p><h3>Secrets</h3><p>True Name: Veylan Voss. Records expunged. Selling curated intel to anonymous buyer in gemstones for six months. Sister Mira believes he's a cloth merchant named 'Daran Wess.' The one crack in his armor.</p><h3>Relationships</h3><p>Quilby 'Quick' Thistledown: Mutual utility, White Mouse dead drop. | Guildmaster Cael: Debt and resentment — saved his life. | Mira Voss (Sister): Genuine love — his one real vulnerability. | Anonymous Buyer: Unknown threat, gemstone payments.</p><h3>Plot Hooks</h3><p>1. Quilby lets slip Needle is seeking someone with the party's skillset — a job that cannot involve guild members.\n2. Anonymous buyer gives Needle ten days: guild vault codes or 'Mira learns everything.'\n3. Brotherhood lieutenant found dead implicating Needle. He's innocent — proof window closing.\n4. Someone using Needle's alias for murders. Framing — or a second 'Needle.'</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
